&lt;P&gt;Cyber Claw flew fast into the Maximal territory. She thought to herself on how she was going to pull her little plan off with Primal. Since Dinobot was dead, she could try a way, but it was almost winging it. He had discovered her before, posing as the ex-predacon. They didn&#39;t take kindly to her, and neither did Dinobot. That much. He hated clones, that she knew. But now, as Carnage said, he was dead, which meant that he wasn&#39;t there to bite her head off. Rat Trap and Optimus Primal&nbsp;was there to do that now. 
&lt;P&gt;She flew closer to the grasslands, a little skittish around the Maximal trailing behind her. She felt out of place without her forest to cover her.&nbsp;As she flew closer and closer, she looked out&nbsp;to see the ship of the Axalon. But it wasn&#39;t there. She squinted, slowing down her flight, and xoomed into the landscape with her sharp optics. She focused in to where&nbsp;the metal mass would be.
&lt;P&gt;She haulted in mid-air. The Axalon was gone.
&lt;P&gt;&quot;What the slagging?&quot; she uttered. She lowered down to the ground, landing on the top of a hill. She studied the area. &quot;Where...&quot;
&lt;P&gt;She looked up, to the Fuzor, then looked behind her for Carnage. She wasn&#39;t there, either.
